Based on my research, the latest MSTest is **4.2.3**. Here are the breaking changes relevant to your code:

## Breaking Changes Affecting Your Project

### 1. `[ExpectedException]` is removed (CRITICAL)
This is your biggest issue. `ExpectedExceptionAttribute` no longer exists in v4. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

### 2. `Assert.IsTrue(true)` now warns (MSTEST0032)
Your `Validate_ValidInput_Succeeds` test will trigger a **warning** (upgraded from Info to Warning in v4). Replace with a meaningful assertion.

### 3. `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed
Not in your code currently, but be aware if you add cleanup later.

### 4. Analyzer severity escalations
Several analyzers are now Warning by default (were Info): MSTEST0007, MSTEST0017, MSTEST0025, MSTEST0032, MSTEST0037, etc.

### 5. `Assert` APIs signature change
`message` + `params object[]` overloads now only accept `message` (use string interpolation instead of format strings).

## To Upgrade

Update your `.csproj`:
```xml
<PackageReference Include="MSTest" Version="4.2.3" />
```

Would you like me to apply these fixes to your project?
